'''Citizen National Guard''', abbreviated as '''CNG''', is a [[Filipino nationalist]] [[political advocacy group]] founded in 2017 by Antonio Valdez. It was established by supporters of Philippine President [[Rodrigo Duterte]]. The group aims to "defend the country, protect the people and support the president", from perceived opponents, including [[Islamic extremism|Islamic]] and [[Communism in the Philippines|communist]] extremists (mainly [[Philippines and ISIL|ISIS]]-inspired groups and [[Communist Party of the Philippines|CPP-NPA]], respectively) and supporters of the [[Liberal Party (Philippines)|Liberal Party]], which is the main [[Opposition (politics)|opposition party]] since Duterte's term.<ref name="dissent">{{Cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/headlines/2017/10/11/1747726/dissent-destabilization-are-same-citizen-national-guard|title=Dissent, destabilization are the same — Citizen National Guard {{!}} Philstar.com|website=philstar.com|access-date=2018-04-11}}</ref>
The group received support from some government officials, including former [[Department of Justice (Philippines)|Department of Justice]] secretary [[Vitaliano Aguirre II]] and Public Attorney's Office Chairperson Persida Acosta. Conversely, its establishment drew criticism from opposition, mainly the [[Left-wing politics|left-leaning]] alliance [[Bagong Alyansang Makabayan]].<ref name="dissent"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/headlines/2017/10/02/1745156/aguirre-acosta-laud-group-will-fight-enemies-state|title=Aguirre, Acosta laud group that will fight|website=philstar.com|access-date=2018-04-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/headlines/2017/10/04/1745578/group-alarmed-creation-citizens-guard-against-enemies-state|title=Group alarmed by creation of 'citizens guard' against enemies of state {{!}} Philstar.com|website=philstar.com|access-date=2018-04-11}}</ref>
